<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.843243>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Pimelodus coprophagus CZUT-IC 7485, 139.9 mm SL, Agulazal creek, Catatumbo River Drainage, Norte de Santander Departament, Lake Maracaibo Basin, Colombia. Photo by J. E. García-Melo." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/843243/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.843245>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Scatter plot illustrating percent head length (HL) vs. premaxilary projection from mandibular symphysis (% GAP) in P. navarroi (squares) compared to P. coprophagus (diamond)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/843245/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.843247>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Distributions of trans-Andean Pimelodus. Symbols may represent more than one collection. Yellow symbols indicate type localities. Pimelodus coprophagus (cross), Pimelodus navarroi (diamond), Pimelodus grosskopfii (pentagon), Pimelodus punctatus (star), Pimelodus crypticus n. sp. (triangle), and Pimelodus yuma n. sp. (circle)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/843247/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

